item.title: PirmaUzduotis
item.description: In physics, mass is a measure of the amount of matter in an object. It is typically represented by the symbol “m” and is measured in kilograms (kg). In most situations, the mass of an object is positive, meaning that it has a positive weight when placed on a scale. However, it is possible to consider the concept of negative mass, which would be an object that has a negative weight and behaves in strange and counterintuitive ways when subjected to forces.
